
        Blue Carbon Ecosystem Research Report
        
        This document contains important information about mangrove ecosystems and their carbon sequestration capabilities.
        
        Key Findings:
        - Mangroves can sequester up to 6.5 Mg C/ha/year
        - Coastal restoration projects show 85% success rate
        - Blue carbon markets are valued at $2.3 billion globally
        
        Methodology:
        Our research involved field studies across 15 coastal sites, measuring carbon storage in sediments and biomass.
        
        Conclusions:
        Mangrove restoration is critical for climate change mitigation and coastal protection.
        